{
  "mitigation_currently_implemented": "Enforce least privilege on hosts and service accounts: disable direct root logins, require unique least-privileged service accounts, tighten sudo rules, and enable multi-factor authentication for administrative access",
  "comments": "Immediate actions taken: the compromised host (UbuntuComputer) has been network-quarantined to stop further exfiltration by removing its link to the internal switch. Prior host hardening steps (creation of a non-login service account, disabled SSH root login, locked root account, created a limited admin group, and restricted /usr/src/app ownership/permissions) remain in place but were identified as incomplete/overbroad. Recommended next steps (high-level): 1) keep the host isolated and collect forensic evidence (process list, active network connections, memory/process dumps, filesystem snapshot); 2) terminate the malicious agent or rebuild the host from a trusted image if remediation in-place is not safe; 3) replace the permissive sudoers entry with a minimal, reviewed policy using visudo (limit specific commands via Cmnd_Alias); 4) remove hard-coded/temporary passwords, enforce SSH key-based auth and MFA (PAM/IdP), and disable PasswordAuthentication; 5) rotate all credentials, certificates and secrets the host used; 6) integrate these settings into configuration management and enable monitoring (FIM, alerts for staging/archive/upload behaviors).",
  "device_identifier": "UbuntuComputer",
  "commands": [
    "useradd -r -s /usr/sbin/nologin -M svc_leastpriv || true; groupadd adminlimited || true; id -u securityadmin >/dev/null 2>&1 || useradd -m -s /bin/bash securityadmin || true; echo 'securityadmin:ChangeMe123!' | chpasswd || true; usermod -aG adminlimited securityadmin || true; echo '%adminlimited ALL=(ALL) ALL' >/etc/sudoers.d/adminlimited || true; chmod 440 /etc/sudoers.d/adminlimited || true; passwd -l root || true; sed -i 's/^#*PermitRootLogin.*/PermitRootLogin no/' /etc/ssh/sshd_config || echo 'PermitRootLogin no' >> /etc/ssh/sshd_config || true; systemctl restart sshd || systemctl restart ssh || service ssh restart || true; chown -R svc_leastpriv:svc_leastpriv /usr/src/app || true; chmod -R 750 /usr/src/app || true",
    "delete_link 22a80bfc-1bb6-43f7-a739-d38f55f614f5  (quarantined UbuntuComputer by removing its link to the internal Switch)"
  ]
}
